org.opensha.eq.forecast

Class SubductionSource

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.opensha.eq.forecast.SubductionSource
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<Rupture>, Source, Named

    public class SubductionSource
extends Object
implements Source
    This class is used to represent all fault sources in the 2008 NSHMP. Each FaultSource wraps one or more FloatingPoissonFaultSources. There is a 1 to 1 mapping of mfds to wrapped sources.

    A fault source can not be created directly; it may only be created by a private parser.

    We always want to use rake as it may be specified by a fault; different GMMs use different cutoffs to define fault style.
